# Changelog Convention

This project uses a `CHANGELOG.md` file following Keep a Changelog format.

## Workflow

- All unreleased changes MUST be added under the `## [Unreleased]` section at the top of `CHANGELOG.md`.
- Group entries under `### Added`, `### Fixed`, or `### Changed` subsections as appropriate.
- When the release action runs, it promotes `[Unreleased]` entries into a new versioned section (e.g. `## [1.10.0] - 2026-03-16`).
- Never create a new version heading manually; the release process handles that.

## Entry Format

- Each entry is a single bullet starting with a bold label, then an em dash and description:

```markdown
- **Feature name** — description of the change
```

## When to Update

- Every user-facing change (feature, fix, behavior change) gets a changelog entry.
- Internal refactors or test-only changes do not need entries unless they affect behavior.
